 astonishing build. Immaculately finished with a fantastic slot-in carbon fibre ‘cut bonnet’ solution, its classic looks are underpinned by modern build techniques. But it was the E30 M3 S14 engine that was the star of the build. Rare as hen’s teeth, I found myself gazing into the engine bay for longer than I’d care to admit…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151550/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-17.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151550/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-17-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-17\" data-attachment-id=\"658024\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151550/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-17.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/12/the-tuning-experience-at-essen-motor-show-2024/ems-24-mc-sh-tex-edits-17/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151550/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-17-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut this early R107 stole my heart like no other car could at EMS this year. It wasn’t the fastest car at the show by any means, but I can’t resist an R107 or any other early Mercedes-Benz SL, for that matter. It also gave me a chance to test my three-pointed star nerdiness out, deducing that this was an early car in Milan Brown produced somewhere between 1975 and ’79.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151546/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-16.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151546/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-16-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-16\" data-attachment-id=\"658023\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151546/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-16.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/12/the-tuning-experience-at-essen-motor-show-2024/ems-24-mc-sh-tex-edits-16/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151546/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-16-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151537/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-14-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-14\" data-attachment-id=\"658021\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151537/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-14.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/12/the-tuning-experience-at-essen-motor-show-2024/ems-24-mc-sh-tex-edits-14/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151537/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-14-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151532/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-13-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-13\" data-attachment-id=\"658020\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151532/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-13.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/12/the-tuning-experience-at-essen-motor-show-2024/ems-24-mc-sh-tex-edits-13/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151532/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-13-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith air suspension, BBS RS wheels, an AMG front valance, and a gorgeous leather interior, this was the car I would have driven away in, no question.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151519/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-10.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151519/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-10-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-10\" data-attachment-id=\"658017\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151519/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-10.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/12/the-tuning-experience-at-essen-motor-show-2024/ems-24-mc-sh-tex-edits-10/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151519/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-10-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhile Essen Motor Show’s Tuning Experience may not have the same vibe as it used to in the basement-level show hall, it’s great to see it still thriving – and with it, the enduring strength of German car culture.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMario Christou\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nInstagram: \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mcwpn\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emcwpn\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mariochristou.world\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emariochristou.world\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://mariochristou.world/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emariochristou.world\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151707/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-32-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"EMS 24 MC SH Tex Edits-32\" data-attachment-id=\"658039\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/05151707/EMS-24-MC-SH-Tex-Edits-32.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" dat